          "version": "polymer_evolution_phase1-3.5",
          "provenance_state": "local_rds"
        }
      ],
      "restrictions": {
        "kind": "cmp",
        "col": "window_bp",
        "op": "=",
        "rhs": 1000000
      },
      "scale_note": "1 Mb resolution, conservation-as-age-proxy. The mechanistic resolution of WHY gBGC GC-enrichment increases rather than decreases deformability is an open question; one hypothesis is that gBGC selects for specific GC-positions (CpG-rich, alternating purine-pyrimidine) that happen to be more flexible than other GC-rich configurations."
    },
